WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.437 --> 00:00:05.497
The name Olivette
means little to you.

2
00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:08.039
High-ranking member
of the Grand Coven.

3
00:00:08.208 --> 00:00:11.440
The one who laid the charge against
me. She's come back to the States.

4
00:00:11.612 --> 00:00:14.172
Now would be an
excellent time to strike.

5
00:00:14.348 --> 00:00:18.615
And take out a miserable old witch who's
been standing in my way for centuries.

6
00:00:18.785 --> 00:00:20.549
CROWLEY: No. that is not happening.
- What?

7
00:00:20.721 --> 00:00:22.622
Something's come
up. Olivette can wait.

8
00:00:22.823 --> 00:00:24.985
My peace is helping
people. Working cases.

9
00:00:25.158 --> 00:00:27.354
- That's all I wanna do.
- Is this about the Mark?

10
00:00:27.528 --> 00:00:30.965
DEAN: I'm done trying to find a cure.
The answer's not out there. It's with me.

11
00:00:31.131 --> 00:00:33.123
I'm gonna fight it
till I can't anymore.

12
00:00:33.333 --> 00:00:36.394
CROWLEY: What are you doing?
- What's it look like? I'm leaving.

13
00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:38.937
Another petty manipulation.

14
00:00:39.106 --> 00:00:40.574
What do you want from me?

15
00:00:40.741 --> 00:00:45.702
Why. it breaks my heart to see what
a colossal numbnut you've become.

16
00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:51.546
Sad. bored wee boy on the throne who will
flop ass-up the second those Winchesters...

17
00:00:51.718 --> 00:00:55.746
hunters. who'd as soon see you
dead as have you to tea. ask you to.

18
00:00:55.923 --> 00:00:58.392
You're their bitch.

19
00:01:04.598 --> 00:01:06.590
[ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:01:07.501 --> 00:01:10.198
TERRY: I detest all my sins
because of thy just punishment...

21
00:01:10.370 --> 00:01:12.896
but most of all because
they offend thee. my God...

22
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:15.599
who art all good and
deserving of all my love.

23
00:01:15.809 --> 00:01:19.075
I firmly resolve with the help
of thy grace. to sin no more...

24
00:01:19.246 --> 00:01:21.841
and to avoid the near
occasion of sin. Amen.

25
00:01:22.015 --> 00:01:23.574
DELANEY: I absolve
you of your sins...

26
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:27.084
in the name of the Father and
of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.

27
00:01:27.254 --> 00:01:28.415
Amen.

28
00:01:28.589 --> 00:01:30.922
Go in peace. Terry.
See you Sunday.

29
00:01:31.592 --> 00:01:33.584
That you will. Father.

30
00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

31
00:02:19.072 --> 00:02:22.907
[SCREAMING]

32
00:02:37.357 --> 00:02:38.689
Majesty.

33
00:02:41.528 --> 00:02:43.656
- I beg you to speak with her.
- What now?

34
00:02:43.864 --> 00:02:46.732
Your mother remains
vexed with your highness...

35
00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:50.337
and vents her frustration
by abusing the court.

36
00:02:50.771 --> 00:02:52.740
No one dares
retaliate. of course.

37
00:02:52.906 --> 00:02:56.001
And. yes. one
expects to suffer in hell.

38
00:02:56.176 --> 00:03:00.773
But I fear I've reached
my limit. To wit:

39
00:03:05.052 --> 00:03:07.112
I mean. seriously.

40
00:03:11.091 --> 00:03:12.525
[SIGHS]

41
00:03:14.528 --> 00:03:15.552
Mother.

42
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:26.298
Yes. Your Royal Highness?

43
00:03:26.506 --> 00:03:28.065
You care to comment?

44
00:03:29.309 --> 00:03:33.770
Magnificent work by an
astonishing talent. Mm-hm. Brava.

45
00:03:39.286 --> 00:03:41.050
I always said you
were two-faced.

46
00:03:42.255 --> 00:03:46.886
Look. Mommy. enough. I
know you're annoyed with me...

47
00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:49.052
Annoyed? No. Fergus.

48
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:54.497
I am devastated. betrayed.
and brokenhearted.

49
00:03:54.668 --> 00:03:57.832
Because I wouldn't go begging to
a bunch of witches on your behalf?

50
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:02.232
The Grand Coven is the
supreme command of all witchcraft.

51
00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:05.504
Without their sanction. I
am forbidden to practice.

52
00:04:05.679 --> 00:04:08.649
- Forgive me. I hadn't noticed you'd stopped.
- That?

53
00:04:08.815 --> 00:04:13.753
Parlor trick. I'm capable of greatness.
Given free reign. I'd be unstoppable.

54
00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:16.822
I am this close to throwing
you back into that dungeon.

55
00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:21.121
Heh. of course. Why not? Why do
anything but cause me more pain?

56
00:04:21.294 --> 00:04:24.287
Bad enough you wouldn't intervene
with Olivette and the Coven...

57
00:04:24.464 --> 00:04:28.731
but you went directly against my
wishes. siding with those Winchesters.

58
00:04:28.902 --> 00:04:32.339
Refusing to kill them. then delivering
the First Blade into their hands...

59
00:04:32.506 --> 00:04:35.203
which you know
could slaughter us all.

60
00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:39.202
You prefer them to
your own flesh and blood.

61
00:04:39.379 --> 00:04:42.645
It's a bitter pill. Fergus.
After all I've done for you.

62
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:45.608
And what exactly would that be?

63
00:04:51.725 --> 00:04:53.694
I gave you life. Fergus.

64
00:04:54.361 --> 00:04:56.159
Without me. sunshine...

65
00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:58.965
you wouldn't exist.

66
00:05:01.168 --> 00:05:02.659
[YELLS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

67
00:05:13.213 --> 00:05:16.615
All right. so I'm thinking.
uh. curse. maybe.

68
00:05:21.721 --> 00:05:23.587
Sam. a little help here. okay?

69
00:05:23.757 --> 00:05:26.886
I'm trying to stay busy. You know.
eye on the ball. not on the Mark.

70
00:05:28.028 --> 00:05:31.021
- This is a case till we know it's not.
- Sure. Yeah. you're right.

71
00:05:31.198 --> 00:05:33.895
- Three suicides. two weeks.
- They're not just suicides.

72
00:05:34.067 --> 00:05:35.330
They gutted themselves.

73
00:05:35.502 --> 00:05:40.202
And they took their sweet time doing it.
I mean. that had to be incredibly painful.

74
00:05:40.373 --> 00:05:42.865
I can't seem to find any
link between the vics either.

75
00:05:43.043 --> 00:05:46.070
Yeah. probably a curse.

76
00:05:49.249 --> 00:05:52.447
SISTER MATHIAS: And
this man. he was handsome?

77
00:05:52.652 --> 00:05:56.851
ISABELLA: Exquisite.
He took my breath away.

78
00:05:58.191 --> 00:06:02.287
But we are told not to speak so much
of the time before we joined the order.

79
00:06:02.462 --> 00:06:06.365
We all found our way
to this life for a reason.

80
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:09.063
Was he yours?

81
00:06:10.604 --> 00:06:15.042
His name was Piero.
An incredible artist.

82
00:06:18.178 --> 00:06:21.637
<i>Sometimes I would pose for him.</i>

83
00:06:21.815 --> 00:06:23.807
<i>And he called me his muse.</i>

84
00:06:25.685 --> 00:06:30.589
<i>As you can imagine. we spent
hours. days with each other.</i>

85
00:06:32.325 --> 00:06:35.193
<i>I felt so free with him.</i>

86
00:06:36.062 --> 00:06:37.928
<i>I...</i>

87
00:06:38.098 --> 00:06:42.433
<i>had never been close
with a man before that.</i>

88
00:06:42.636 --> 00:06:44.036
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

89
00:06:45.639 --> 00:06:48.768
So. what happened?

90
00:06:48.942 --> 00:06:53.437
I... I can't right now.

91
00:06:53.613 --> 00:06:55.411
It's okay.

92
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:57.107
Really.

93
00:06:57.851 --> 00:07:01.219
We're a lot alike. You know?

94
00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:04.023
I think...

95
00:07:05.125 --> 00:07:09.119
we're supposed to
enter the convent...

96
00:07:09.296 --> 00:07:11.288
for some higher purpose.

97
00:07:12.832 --> 00:07:15.131
But many of us chose this...

98
00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:20.038
because of the things...

99
00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:22.734
that overwhelmed us.

100
00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:27.247
So. what do we got? Terry Sloan.

101
00:07:27.414 --> 00:07:30.043
Ordinary guy. not a lot of
friends. but no known enemies.

102
00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:32.344
No relation to the other vics.

103
00:07:32.519 --> 00:07:35.956
Well. not necessarily. He's
Catholic. and so are the other two.

104
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.146
This is Massachusetts.

105
00:07:37.324 --> 00:07:40.658
There are a lot of Catholics in
Massachusetts. You think this is a case?

106
00:07:40.827 --> 00:07:42.557
Who kills himself
with a candlestick?

107
00:07:42.729 --> 00:07:45.358
- There's a billion better ways.
- But he did kill himself.

108
00:07:45.532 --> 00:07:48.832
So he's not a witch. There
was nothing hexxy found on him.

109
00:07:49.002 --> 00:07:50.698
Uh. possession? Could
have been a demon.

110
00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:55.968
The point of a demon possessing a living
thing is to. you know. possess a living thing.

111
00:07:56.142 --> 00:07:59.601
Okay. agent. Why don't you get that
phone back to the Bureau's crime lab...

112
00:07:59.779 --> 00:08:04.012
and get it hacked like you told those guys?
We'll figure out what's going on with Terry.

113
00:08:04.184 --> 00:08:07.518
- Probably nude selfies.
- I'm feeling good about this.

114
00:08:09.089 --> 00:08:10.580
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

115
00:08:10.757 --> 00:08:12.419
[WOMAN COUGHING]

116
00:08:19.399 --> 00:08:20.423
Amen.

117
00:08:46.026 --> 00:08:47.892
[FOOTSTEPS]

118
00:08:53.633 --> 00:08:55.261
Hi. sweetie.

119
00:08:56.169 --> 00:08:57.637
You need to come to bed. Frank.

120
00:08:57.837 --> 00:09:01.069
You gotta be exhausted from all
those night hours you been putting in.

121
00:09:01.241 --> 00:09:04.405
Yup. yup. The old job's gotten
pretty demanding. all right.

122
00:09:17.424 --> 00:09:19.416
Liar.

123
00:09:21.995 --> 00:09:24.658
[BOTH GRUNTING]

124
00:09:38.645 --> 00:09:42.548
LISA: Oh. my God. No. No. Frank!

125
00:09:42.715 --> 00:09:44.775
[LISA SCREAMS]

126
00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:51.088
DELANEY: I just can't believe Lisa
McCarthy would murder her husband.

127
00:09:51.257 --> 00:09:53.920
SAM: Right. Well. his
blood was all over her body...

128
00:09:54.094 --> 00:09:57.462
and her prints were all over
the scissors that butchered him.

129
00:09:57.630 --> 00:09:59.098
- It's terrible.
- Yeah.

130
00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:02.429
We also have some questions.
For starters. she has no memory of it.

131
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:06.232
The last thing she remembers is being
here. Frank had gone to confession.

132
00:10:06.406 --> 00:10:10.434
SAM: So if he happened to say anything
in the confession about. you know...

133
00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:12.238
maybe problems with the wife...

134
00:10:12.412 --> 00:10:14.452
I'm sorry. the nature of
confession is confidential.

135
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:15.843
Ah.

136
00:10:16.015 --> 00:10:19.417
Father. all of the victims
attended your church.

137
00:10:19.586 --> 00:10:22.613
Could you at least tell us if
they'd recently been to confession?

138
00:10:22.789 --> 00:10:27.420
Yes. these men were fairly regular. But
then. so are the majority of the folks here.

139
00:10:27.594 --> 00:10:28.960
- Father? DELANEY: Agents...

140
00:10:29.129 --> 00:10:32.190
Sister Mathias is our
director of social services.

141
00:10:32.398 --> 00:10:35.334
I've asked her to show you
around and answer any questions.

142
00:10:35.768 --> 00:10:37.430
Sure.

143
00:10:37.770 --> 00:10:40.330
DEAN: Sister.
- Agent...?

144
00:10:41.808 --> 00:10:44.710
Allman. And this is Agent Betts.

145
00:10:45.411 --> 00:10:48.506
Sister. you're aware of the
recent string of deaths. right?

146
00:10:48.681 --> 00:10:51.344
Yes. A terrible tragedy.

147
00:10:51.518 --> 00:10:55.216
But I'm confused as
to why you're here.

148
00:10:55.421 --> 00:10:58.220
These were all
suicides. weren't they?

149
00:10:58.424 --> 00:11:00.154
Well. possibly not.

150
00:11:01.227 --> 00:11:02.320
Murders?

151
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:05.294
Well. the actual method
of killing was all identical.

152
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:07.429
Ah. the MO.

153
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:11.137
Yes. indeed. the MO. heh.

154
00:11:13.206 --> 00:11:15.471
I'm gonna go. uh. ahem.
have a look around.

155
00:11:16.643 --> 00:11:19.169
Excuse me. sister.
Agent Betts... Allman.

156
00:11:19.345 --> 00:11:21.337
Ahem. Okay.

157
00:11:22.649 --> 00:11:27.713
Sister. did you notice any
change in the McCarthys' lives?

158
00:11:27.887 --> 00:11:30.356
Fighting. drinking. cheating?
You know. the usual.

159
00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:33.652
"The usual"? A
bit cynical. agent?

160
00:11:33.826 --> 00:11:37.661
Scissors to the gut really
bring out the grinch in me.

161
00:11:39.232 --> 00:11:41.133
Oh...

162
00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:47.572
Now. Lisa McCarthy said that they
were very devoted to each other.

163
00:11:47.740 --> 00:11:51.040
- Was that true?
- That always appeared to be the case.

164
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:55.842
- But...?
- We're looking for a motive. aren't we?

165
00:11:57.083 --> 00:11:58.107
We are.

166
00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:01.119
An earlier victim's cell
phone showed angry texts...

167
00:12:01.287 --> 00:12:05.054
between he and his girlfriend
because he'd been fooling around.

168
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:09.686
- There were rumors.
- So Frank cheated on Lisa? So she lied to me?

169
00:12:11.531 --> 00:12:14.626
- Or she didn't know?
- My sources are excellent.

170
00:12:14.801 --> 00:12:17.635
- And you didn't hear it from me.
- Oh.

171
00:12:22.075 --> 00:12:24.943
[DEVICE WHIRRING]

172
00:12:26.646 --> 00:12:30.014
I got a question.
How does someone...

173
00:12:30.717 --> 00:12:34.154
uh. like you. end
up. you know...?

174
00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:37.051
Cloistered away
from the world. heh?

175
00:12:37.223 --> 00:12:41.923
- Are you making fun of me. Agent Allman?
- No. No. no. I. uh...

176
00:12:42.328 --> 00:12:45.230
I guess I'm just wondering
how somebody quits...

177
00:12:45.398 --> 00:12:48.766
one life for something
completely different...

178
00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:51.029
and then believe in it so much.

179
00:12:52.071 --> 00:12:53.835
Well...

180
00:12:54.741 --> 00:12:58.303
in my case. I felt
I had no choice.

181
00:12:58.478 --> 00:13:02.574
My life had become painful.

182
00:13:03.049 --> 00:13:04.915
There was hopelessness.

183
00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:12.950
I felt I had to find something
larger than myself to focus on.

184
00:13:13.359 --> 00:13:16.989
A kind of mission. I guess.

185
00:13:19.265 --> 00:13:23.066
You have no idea what
I'm talking about. I'm sure.

186
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:25.938
Don't be.

187
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:29.605
SAM: Sister? A question.

188
00:13:30.510 --> 00:13:32.138
I'm sure it's a
different question.

189
00:13:33.079 --> 00:13:35.378
Is there a cemetery nearby?

190
00:13:35.581 --> 00:13:39.450
You could say that. The entire
church is built over burial crypts.

191
00:13:39.619 --> 00:13:45.115
Oh. And have you ever heard or
felt anything strange or unusual?

192
00:13:45.291 --> 00:13:47.226
Unusual how?

193
00:13:47.393 --> 00:13:52.354
Spots in the building that suddenly get
cold. Or maybe you feel like you're not...

194
00:13:52.532 --> 00:13:53.727
Not quite alone.

195
00:13:53.900 --> 00:13:57.598
Rattling chains and teacups
that fly across the room?

196
00:13:58.304 --> 00:14:00.205
Sister. are you
making fun of me?

197
00:14:01.207 --> 00:14:04.644
Really? The FBI
believes in ghosts?

198
00:14:05.978 --> 00:14:07.537
I'm afraid I don't.

199
00:14:08.314 --> 00:14:11.546
If you'll excuse me. agents.
I have to get back to work.

200
00:14:12.018 --> 00:14:13.486
SAM: Mm.

201
00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:22.227
Tell me you didn't think that nun was hot.
I think she had a little thing for me too.

202
00:14:22.395 --> 00:14:25.160
Dean. she was married to Jesus.

203
00:14:25.998 --> 00:14:29.992
All right. so Frank cheated
on his wife. Lisa. All right?

204
00:14:30.169 --> 00:14:32.263
The whole theme of this case...

205
00:14:32.438 --> 00:14:34.930
seems to be about guys
doing their women wrong.

206
00:14:35.141 --> 00:14:36.734
- Notice that?
- Yeah.

207
00:14:36.909 --> 00:14:40.846
But Lisa McCarthy was pretty convincing
she had no idea she killed her husband.

208
00:14:41.013 --> 00:14:43.710
Hot nun said Lisa had no
idea he was cheating on her.

209
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:46.352
Maybe she was controlled
by someone who did.

210
00:14:46.519 --> 00:14:48.112
Again. nothing witchy.

211
00:14:48.287 --> 00:14:49.949
- Ghost?
- Hard to say.

212
00:14:50.156 --> 00:14:53.217
There's EMF in the church.
but it's built on a burial ground.

213
00:14:53.426 --> 00:14:55.861
You know all the victims
recently went to confession.

214
00:14:56.429 --> 00:15:00.332
- You think Father Delaney's involved?
- Or something surrounding the confessional.

215
00:15:01.067 --> 00:15:03.502
Sammy. how long has it
been since my last confession?

216
00:15:03.669 --> 00:15:05.433
You've never been to confession.

217
00:15:05.605 --> 00:15:07.801
Well. that's too long.

218
00:15:11.144 --> 00:15:13.340
You summoned?

219
00:15:13.513 --> 00:15:16.347
Royal Highness.

220
00:15:16.516 --> 00:15:19.509
- Mother.
- Oh. he remembers.

221
00:15:19.719 --> 00:15:23.656
- What can I do for you?
- It's what I can do for you.

222
00:15:25.725 --> 00:15:31.460
I've been thinking just how wretched
it would be if my own raison d'être...

223
00:15:31.631 --> 00:15:35.329
wreaking havoc and pain
on Earth. were taken from me.

224
00:15:36.302 --> 00:15:40.797
I see how stifled you
must feel. And I sympathize.

225
00:15:41.274 --> 00:15:44.733
Does this mean that you'll go to
the Grand Coven on my behalf?

226
00:15:46.746 --> 00:15:48.772
Even better.

227
00:15:49.882 --> 00:15:52.852
I've brought the Coven to you.

228
00:15:53.486 --> 00:15:58.254
I believe you know Olivette.
High Priestess of the Grand Coven.

229
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:02.554
Speechless with joy?

230
00:16:07.567 --> 00:16:10.503
You utter bitch.

231
00:16:10.670 --> 00:16:11.797
Bottom feeder.

232
00:16:12.004 --> 00:16:14.564
Ah. The storm before the storm.

233
00:16:14.774 --> 00:16:18.074
As you can see. the iron
chains render her powerless...

234
00:16:18.277 --> 00:16:21.679
so you can plead your
case. exact your revenge.

235
00:16:21.848 --> 00:16:26.183
Whatever it is that puts a spring back
in your step. You kids have fun now.

236
00:16:30.089 --> 00:16:35.050
I see your time as outcast has
led you from vile to loathsome.

237
00:16:35.228 --> 00:16:39.723
I doubt this strategy of insults
will get you out of this pickle.

238
00:16:39.899 --> 00:16:46.066
Hmm. No. I do not grovel before she who
lay with a Non-Magic and hatched his spawn.

239
00:16:46.439 --> 00:16:48.840
My personal life was
none of your business.

240
00:16:50.243 --> 00:16:51.836
I could've been your superstar.

241
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:53.274
Oh. please.

242
00:16:53.446 --> 00:16:55.938
When we initiated your
thankless ass into the Coven...

243
00:16:56.115 --> 00:16:59.517
we did overlook your private
lapses because of your talent.

244
00:16:59.685 --> 00:17:02.177
We thought you'd outgrow
your reckless. selfish ways.

245
00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.790
But. oh. no. they just
grew out of control.

246
00:17:04.957 --> 00:17:08.724
And now look at you.
Consorting with demons.

247
00:17:08.895 --> 00:17:11.126
Quite the speech.

248
00:17:13.633 --> 00:17:17.070
Considering you're
in my son's palace.

249
00:17:18.938 --> 00:17:19.962
What?

250
00:17:21.274 --> 00:17:25.234
You see. my son. the
spawn you speak of...

251
00:17:25.411 --> 00:17:27.573
is now the king of hell.

252
00:17:27.747 --> 00:17:30.376
Total Cinderella story. I'd say.

253
00:17:31.350 --> 00:17:33.080
Oh. aye.

254
00:17:33.252 --> 00:17:36.416
And now you. dearest Olivette...

255
00:17:36.589 --> 00:17:40.253
are prisoner of the
baddest of the bad.

256
00:17:40.426 --> 00:17:43.157
And his devoted Mommy.

257
00:17:43.362 --> 00:17:47.129
It was the sadness in your eyes.

258
00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:49.865
I saw myself there.

259
00:17:50.369 --> 00:17:52.634
Was it Piero?

260
00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:55.003
Is he the reason you're here?

261
00:17:55.174 --> 00:17:58.975
There is not much difference
between madness and devotion.

262
00:17:59.378 --> 00:18:02.143
I was obsessed with him.

263
00:18:04.517 --> 00:18:07.453
<i>We shared each other's secrets.</i>

264
00:18:07.653 --> 00:18:09.918
<i>We were on the same road.</i>

265
00:18:10.156 --> 00:18:15.151
<i>I suddenly realized how deeply
in love with Piero I had fallen.</i>

266
00:18:16.495 --> 00:18:20.762
<i>He said it was only after I posed for
him that his work took on real power...</i>

267
00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.993
<i>real expression.</i>

268
00:18:23.803 --> 00:18:28.434
<i>The painting I had posed for
was the beginning of his career.</i>

269
00:18:29.408 --> 00:18:31.570
<i>In the end. it was
his masterpiece.</i>

270
00:18:31.744 --> 00:18:33.645
[BELL TOLLING]

271
00:18:42.421 --> 00:18:49.294
Sweet Jesus. Nothing in my
love life was ever so magical.

272
00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:51.658
Magic can be ruinous.

273
00:18:51.831 --> 00:18:53.993
Especially if the
trick is on you.

274
00:18:54.867 --> 00:18:58.531
<i>I finally confessed
my heart to Piero.</i>

275
00:18:58.838 --> 00:19:01.467
<i>I felt we could read
each other's thoughts.</i>

276
00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:06.443
<i>But I said the words
inside out loud. "I love you."</i>

277
00:19:06.879 --> 00:19:10.213
<i>I waited. dying inside.</i>

278
00:19:10.383 --> 00:19:11.976
<i>And then...</i>

279
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:15.549
<i>he explained he
had feelings for me...</i>

280
00:19:16.022 --> 00:19:18.548
<i>but not of the same sort.</i>

281
00:19:21.527 --> 00:19:23.052
He loved another?

282
00:19:24.030 --> 00:19:25.521
Indeed.

283
00:19:25.698 --> 00:19:26.961
His art.

284
00:19:27.700 --> 00:19:29.965
It was everything to him.

285
00:19:30.836 --> 00:19:34.568
Insomuch that I affected
it. he cared for me.

286
00:19:34.740 --> 00:19:38.541
But beyond that. he could
offer me nothing but friendship.

287
00:19:40.713 --> 00:19:43.114
I fell into such despair.

288
00:19:43.282 --> 00:19:46.377
I could not eat. nor sleep.

289
00:19:47.086 --> 00:19:49.715
Until my family
could stand no more.

290
00:19:49.889 --> 00:19:53.121
And that's when you
entered the convent.

291
00:19:53.292 --> 00:19:55.352
It's as if I'd died.

292
00:19:56.195 --> 00:20:00.690
My father sent me there to
escape my sorrow and forget Piero.

293
00:20:01.100 --> 00:20:04.195
His servants dragged
me from home one night.

294
00:20:06.238 --> 00:20:08.867
All these things from
my father's estate...

295
00:20:09.041 --> 00:20:11.442
I never saw them
again after that night.

296
00:20:11.610 --> 00:20:14.944
Everything that was
mine was lost to me.

297
00:20:16.415 --> 00:20:18.008
Except my journal.

298
00:20:19.585 --> 00:20:22.214
Things I could say to no one.

299
00:20:22.888 --> 00:20:24.789
Things no one wanted to hear.

300
00:20:26.759 --> 00:20:30.389
- Loneliness is...
- Yes.

301
00:20:31.097 --> 00:20:32.895
It is.

302
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:45.405
Really can't say I'm surprised.
You always were petulant.

303
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:48.673
And reckless. And overrated.

304
00:20:48.848 --> 00:20:51.010
Banishment was too good for you.

305
00:20:51.183 --> 00:20:52.811
[BOTH GRUNTING]

306
00:20:55.554 --> 00:20:58.456
You were always so
envious of my skills.

307
00:20:59.058 --> 00:21:01.823
You fool. The only threat I
ever posed to the Coven...

308
00:21:01.994 --> 00:21:04.361
was that I was smarter.
more gifted than you.

309
00:21:04.563 --> 00:21:07.658
- More blindly ambitious.
- Why not?

310
00:21:07.833 --> 00:21:09.995
You nits were content
to live in the shadows...

311
00:21:10.169 --> 00:21:15.130
dicking around with black cats and
broomsticks instead of greatness.

312
00:21:15.307 --> 00:21:17.242
[OLIVETTE GRUNTS THEN PANTS]

313
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:22.312
- What was that one for?
- Emphasis.

314
00:21:24.283 --> 00:21:26.377
I will get what I want from you.

315
00:21:26.585 --> 00:21:27.780
No. you won't.

316
00:21:27.953 --> 00:21:31.014
Because what you are
looking for no longer exists.

317
00:21:31.490 --> 00:21:34.949
The Coven is a pale
relic of its past power.

318
00:21:35.127 --> 00:21:39.394
Weakened by witch hunts. burning
at the stake. endless persecution.

319
00:21:39.598 --> 00:21:42.500
- And all of it was engineered by them.
- "Them"?

320
00:21:42.668 --> 00:21:44.967
Oh. ha-ha-ha.

321
00:21:45.137 --> 00:21:47.368
You're not as quick
as I'd have thought.

322
00:21:47.706 --> 00:21:48.730
All right.

323
00:21:49.141 --> 00:21:54.546
It's a rabid group of sanctimonious
do-gooders dedicated to our downfall.

324
00:21:55.147 --> 00:21:57.981
- They had equal magic?
- Worse.

325
00:21:58.150 --> 00:22:00.551
Public relations.

326
00:22:01.487 --> 00:22:04.651
They whipped the church
and public into a panic.

327
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:07.016
Our best were killed
or driven underground.

328
00:22:07.193 --> 00:22:10.027
They then plundered
our spells and secrets...

329
00:22:10.196 --> 00:22:13.655
and shipped them to hidden
bunkers all around the world.

330
00:22:13.833 --> 00:22:15.893
It appears you hate them
more than you do me.

331
00:22:16.068 --> 00:22:18.936
They tried to destroy our world.

332
00:22:19.138 --> 00:22:23.405
Hoarding unbelievable power
for their own amusement.

333
00:22:25.911 --> 00:22:28.904
Smug. self-righteous bastards.

334
00:22:29.081 --> 00:22:31.641
The Men of Letters.

335
00:22:35.087 --> 00:22:36.612
[KNOCKING]

336
00:22:36.789 --> 00:22:38.348
Yes?

337
00:22:38.924 --> 00:22:40.552
Hi. Father.

338
00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:42.587
Pardon me?

339
00:22:43.028 --> 00:22:45.463
Pardon you? I thought it was
the other way around. heh.

340
00:22:45.664 --> 00:22:47.064
Just...

341
00:22:47.266 --> 00:22:52.569
Ahem. So I'm here to clean house.
Need to get some things off my chest.

342
00:22:52.738 --> 00:22:54.900
Oh. All right.

343
00:22:55.207 --> 00:22:57.176
- Continue.
- Um...

344
00:22:58.744 --> 00:23:00.804
It's the women. Father.

345
00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:03.140
Where do I begin. heh?

346
00:23:03.315 --> 00:23:06.251
"Bless me Father. for I
have sinned." is usual.

347
00:23:07.253 --> 00:23:11.554
Right. Good.
Yeah. So that. and...

348
00:23:13.058 --> 00:23:16.825
So the women. And this is
not something I am proud of.

349
00:23:16.996 --> 00:23:20.728
But I let them think that we
have more of a future than we do.

350
00:23:21.934 --> 00:23:23.596
You know?

351
00:23:23.769 --> 00:23:25.635
Ugh. Gina.

352
00:23:26.305 --> 00:23:27.739
Gina?

353
00:23:28.407 --> 00:23:32.071
Don't get me wrong. I mean.
she was... It was good times.

354
00:23:32.244 --> 00:23:36.773
You know how it is. The sex. the
lasagna. But I was not honest with her.

355
00:23:36.949 --> 00:23:40.283
Sometimes I was seeing two.
maybe three girls at the same time.

356
00:23:40.452 --> 00:23:43.820
Sometimes in the same
day. Heh. You get the picture.

357
00:23:45.024 --> 00:23:48.483
And it wasn't just
Gina. It was endless.

358
00:23:50.262 --> 00:23:53.630
- It's making me sick.
- And you wish to be forgiven. my son?

359
00:23:53.799 --> 00:23:55.427
I do. I need to clean up my act.

360
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:58.594
As penance. you shall say five
"Hail Marys." two "Our Fathers"...

361
00:23:58.771 --> 00:24:00.797
and reflect on
your transgression.

362
00:24:00.973 --> 00:24:02.839
And then that's it?
Then I'm good to go?

363
00:24:03.008 --> 00:24:07.378
One would hope some
inner exploration might occur.

364
00:24:07.546 --> 00:24:12.450
The prayers are just the beginning
to some serious soul-searching.

365
00:24:12.618 --> 00:24:14.018
DEAN: Hmm.

366
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:20.616
Anything else on your
mind. Agent Allman?

367
00:24:25.798 --> 00:24:26.857
[SCOFFS]

368
00:24:29.902 --> 00:24:31.871
What if I said...

369
00:24:32.905 --> 00:24:35.204
I didn't wanna die?

370
00:24:35.574 --> 00:24:39.875
- Yet. You know. that I wasn't ready.
- Are you expecting to?

371
00:24:42.514 --> 00:24:44.346
Always.

372
00:24:45.050 --> 00:24:48.282
The life I live. the work I do.

373
00:24:49.822 --> 00:24:53.987
I pretty much just figured that that
was all there was to me. you know.

374
00:24:54.193 --> 00:24:56.219
I tear around...

375
00:24:56.795 --> 00:25:01.096
and jam the key in the ignition.
and haul ass until I ran out of gas.

376
00:25:02.001 --> 00:25:06.268
I guess I just thought sooner or
later I'd go out the same way that I live.

377
00:25:06.438 --> 00:25:09.169
Pedal to the metal.
and that would be it.

378
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.208
But now?

379
00:25:15.347 --> 00:25:17.816
Now. um...

380
00:25:18.450 --> 00:25:22.387
some recent events...

381
00:25:24.089 --> 00:25:27.582
made me think I might be
closer to that than I really thought.

382
00:25:29.428 --> 00:25:31.021
And...

383
00:25:32.197 --> 00:25:35.725
I don't know. I mean.
you know. there's things...

384
00:25:36.635 --> 00:25:39.764
there's people.
feelings that I...

385
00:25:41.273 --> 00:25:43.902
I wanna experience
differently than I had before.

386
00:25:44.076 --> 00:25:46.944
Or maybe even
for the first time.

387
00:25:47.112 --> 00:25:50.571
Go a little deeper
perhaps than with Gina?

388
00:25:52.651 --> 00:25:54.142
Yeah.

389
00:25:54.787 --> 00:25:56.756
Yeah. I'm just
starting to think...

390
00:25:58.724 --> 00:26:01.489
that maybe there's more
to it all than I thought.

391
00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:05.595
Learning there's more to the
universe than your tiny world...

392
00:26:05.764 --> 00:26:07.790
can be a frightening discovery.

393
00:26:09.635 --> 00:26:12.434
Do you truly believe
in God. agent?

394
00:26:13.906 --> 00:26:16.808
Because that can be a comfort.

395
00:26:19.311 --> 00:26:21.974
I believe there is a God.

396
00:26:25.918 --> 00:26:29.013
But I am not sure
he still believes in us.

397
00:26:44.770 --> 00:26:45.931
So?

398
00:26:46.105 --> 00:26:48.973
- Think you had an eavesdropper in there?
- Hope so.

399
00:26:49.141 --> 00:26:51.167
Better watch your
back. If we're right...

400
00:26:51.343 --> 00:26:54.541
jerks like you are just
what our ghost is looking for.

401
00:27:08.694 --> 00:27:10.560
Isabella?

402
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:20.736
Isabella? Are you here?

403
00:27:55.407 --> 00:27:59.503
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

404
00:28:02.614 --> 00:28:07.552
ISABELLA: <i>I found no peace in the
convent. and my sorrow turned to rage.</i>

405
00:28:07.719 --> 00:28:11.019
<i>What was once love for
Piero had become hatred.</i>

406
00:28:12.558 --> 00:28:16.290
<i>One night I snuck out a window
and made my way to his studio.</i>

407
00:28:17.262 --> 00:28:22.030
<i>I'm not sure why I
went. To confront him?</i>

408
00:28:22.501 --> 00:28:25.733
<i>To ruin the painting and destroy
his love the way he destroyed mine?</i>

409
00:28:25.904 --> 00:28:27.839
[MAN AND WOMAN MOANING]

410
00:28:28.006 --> 00:28:29.736
<i>There they were.</i>

411
00:28:51.930 --> 00:28:54.661
[SCREAMING]

412
00:28:54.833 --> 00:28:56.699
Isabella.

413
00:28:56.868 --> 00:28:58.928
[PIERO GRUNTING]

414
00:29:15.153 --> 00:29:18.487
I never mentioned her to you
because it didn't occur to me...

415
00:29:18.657 --> 00:29:21.092
she was connected
with the murders.

416
00:29:21.260 --> 00:29:24.719
Ever since I've been here. I've
come across restless spirits of all sorts.

417
00:29:24.896 --> 00:29:26.159
They're all kind of...

418
00:29:26.331 --> 00:29:28.960
sad. Harmless.

419
00:29:29.134 --> 00:29:32.229
And eventually the poor
things go to their final rest.

420
00:29:32.404 --> 00:29:36.136
Wait a second. So you're just
comfortable around ghosts?

421
00:29:36.308 --> 00:29:40.006
As a spiritual person. I've
accepted many planes of existence.

422
00:29:40.178 --> 00:29:44.138
And as I said. they've
all been harmless.

423
00:29:48.587 --> 00:29:51.853
Isabella was my friend.

424
00:29:52.257 --> 00:29:54.658
We had a lot in common.

425
00:29:54.826 --> 00:29:56.624
Including...

426
00:29:57.062 --> 00:29:59.327
painful love lives.

427
00:29:59.498 --> 00:30:01.831
I wanted to protect her.

428
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:05.334
You said she showed up three weeks
ago when stuff from her home arrived?

429
00:30:05.504 --> 00:30:09.134
Yes. Part of a shipment
from a monastery in Tivoli.

430
00:30:09.308 --> 00:30:12.642
Her family's treasures
found their way to the Church.

431
00:30:12.811 --> 00:30:14.905
As with many of the
great houses of Europe.

432
00:30:15.080 --> 00:30:18.209
You get that she got here just
before the murders started happening?

433
00:30:18.383 --> 00:30:21.785
I finally realized that.

434
00:30:21.953 --> 00:30:27.859
And then I heard the two of
you. and it made me wonder.

435
00:30:28.593 --> 00:30:31.188
That's when I read her journal.

436
00:30:31.363 --> 00:30:34.299
It was given to her
father right after her death.

437
00:30:35.100 --> 00:30:38.969
- Vengeful spirit. Just like we thought.
- Yeah. but 16th-century Florence.

438
00:30:39.137 --> 00:30:41.470
- She's probably buried in Florence.
- I assume.

439
00:30:42.808 --> 00:30:45.676
The journal ended
right after her trial.

440
00:30:46.211 --> 00:30:49.545
Piero's death was so horrific...

441
00:30:49.715 --> 00:30:51.741
she was convicted of witchcraft.

442
00:30:51.917 --> 00:30:53.818
They sentenced her
to burn at the stake.

443
00:30:53.985 --> 00:30:56.545
If she burned. then
so would her bones.

444
00:30:56.722 --> 00:31:00.386
Yeah. but. Dean. something here is
the tether that ties her to this place.

445
00:31:00.559 --> 00:31:03.552
It's probably the journal.
Where she wrote about her life.

446
00:31:03.729 --> 00:31:06.858
Why don't we see if we can't find
Isabella and try to slow her down?

447
00:31:07.032 --> 00:31:10.662
- And. Sam. burn all this stuff.
- Her journal?

448
00:31:12.137 --> 00:31:14.732
- Is that necessary?
- Believe me. it's necessary.

449
00:31:14.906 --> 00:31:17.171
I don't know. There
might be more in here.

450
00:31:17.342 --> 00:31:19.777
Sam. burn it. Let's go.

451
00:31:25.584 --> 00:31:27.712
[BOTH GRUNTING]

452
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:31.288
I'm telling you. I
don't know any more.

453
00:31:31.456 --> 00:31:32.754
You're lying.

454
00:31:33.158 --> 00:31:37.892
Just as you lied about me all these years. You're
afraid I'll recover all the stolen potions...

455
00:31:38.063 --> 00:31:40.362
and spells and become
more powerful than you.

456
00:31:40.532 --> 00:31:42.967
Oh. poor. poor Rowena.

457
00:31:43.168 --> 00:31:46.263
Always the victim of one
conspiracy or another.

458
00:31:46.438 --> 00:31:50.432
You're so consumed with your
rise to power. you can't see the truth.

459
00:31:50.609 --> 00:31:52.874
I see the truth.
And it's pathetic.

460
00:31:53.044 --> 00:31:57.812
You let these Men of Letters pillage the
greatest trove of magical secrets in the world...

461
00:31:57.983 --> 00:32:00.714
- and did nothing.
- Ow!

462
00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:03.879
We were weakened.

463
00:32:04.055 --> 00:32:08.652
The plunder was dispersed
to bunkers all around the world.

464
00:32:08.827 --> 00:32:12.821
Those bunkers are powerfully warded.
There was nothing we could do to stop them.

465
00:32:12.998 --> 00:32:16.230
How do I find the
Men of Letters?

466
00:32:16.401 --> 00:32:18.393
I don't even know if
they exist anymore.

467
00:32:19.805 --> 00:32:23.901
I've heard that the American
chapter was extinguished in the 1950s.

468
00:32:24.075 --> 00:32:27.136
But apparently two
of its members survive.

469
00:32:28.613 --> 00:32:31.947
The hunters. Sam
and Dean Winchester.

470
00:32:32.117 --> 00:32:33.517
The Winchesters?

471
00:32:36.521 --> 00:32:39.013
Again with the Winchesters.

472
00:32:39.224 --> 00:32:43.423
Perpetually the Winchesters.

473
00:32:46.298 --> 00:32:47.789
Olivette. dear...

474
00:32:50.669 --> 00:32:57.542
pleasant though this little chat
has been. I feel it's come to a close.

475
00:32:58.276 --> 00:33:03.874
What you're telling me is that the Coven
is no longer all-powerful. and therefore...

476
00:33:04.049 --> 00:33:06.484
that you are no longer useful.

477
00:33:06.651 --> 00:33:09.143
You'd better be careful. Rowena.

478
00:33:09.321 --> 00:33:11.950
There's a line that
cannot be crossed.

479
00:33:12.123 --> 00:33:15.787
Witch-on-witch murder is
anathema to the community.

480
00:33:15.961 --> 00:33:17.793
The community. heh?

481
00:33:18.330 --> 00:33:19.628
Who needs them?

482
00:33:20.532 --> 00:33:24.993
To think of all the years
I've lived in fear for nothing.

483
00:33:27.372 --> 00:33:30.171
You ruined my life. Olivette.

484
00:33:31.376 --> 00:33:34.369
And you shall pay with yours.

485
00:33:38.149 --> 00:33:40.983
Rowena. please. you
don't want to do this.

486
00:33:41.152 --> 00:33:43.678
[ROWENA HUMMING]

487
00:33:43.855 --> 00:33:46.017
Please. Rowena. don't do this.

488
00:33:47.659 --> 00:33:49.355
Rowena. please.

489
00:33:50.929 --> 00:33:52.124
Please. stop.

490
00:33:52.297 --> 00:33:55.131
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

491
00:33:57.102 --> 00:33:59.094
[GROANING AND SCREAMING]

492
00:33:59.271 --> 00:34:01.365
[CHUCKLES]

493
00:34:03.208 --> 00:34:05.143
[LAUGHS THEN GASPS]

494
00:34:07.178 --> 00:34:09.374
I haven't thought this through.

495
00:34:09.548 --> 00:34:13.007
Why should I kill you and
give you an easy way out...

496
00:34:13.184 --> 00:34:16.621
when there are
far better options?

497
00:34:18.924 --> 00:34:21.450
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

498
00:34:21.626 --> 00:34:24.619
No. No. No!

499
00:34:24.829 --> 00:34:27.196
Rowena. please. No...

500
00:34:28.166 --> 00:34:29.361
[CHUCKLES]

501
00:34:29.834 --> 00:34:32.599
Oh. I'm a genius.

502
00:34:33.572 --> 00:34:38.772
I don't see how she could murder these
people if she was tethered to the church.

503
00:34:38.944 --> 00:34:43.848
She could possess a person inside the church.
ride out. and get yanked back after the kill.

504
00:34:44.382 --> 00:34:47.784
And can ghosts be shot?

505
00:34:48.486 --> 00:34:51.854
This is rock salt. If we
spot her. it'll slow her down.

506
00:34:57.062 --> 00:35:00.624
ISABELLA: <i>and as the days
passed. my love for Piero deepened...</i>

507
00:35:00.799 --> 00:35:03.359
<i>as did his belief in my
powers as his muse.</i>

508
00:35:04.769 --> 00:35:07.295
<i>He said he wanted
something from me...</i>

509
00:35:07.472 --> 00:35:10.499
<i>something he could
barely give voice to.</i>

510
00:35:10.942 --> 00:35:13.810
<i>He thought the effect I had
on his work was profound.</i>

511
00:35:15.180 --> 00:35:17.649
<i>He had never
painted so well before.</i>

512
00:35:17.816 --> 00:35:21.981
<i>He asked if he might have a bit of
my blood to mix into the pigment.</i>

513
00:35:23.588 --> 00:35:26.581
<i>Piero was so afraid
he would hurt me.</i>

514
00:35:26.758 --> 00:35:30.092
<i>I told him. on the contrary.
it was my great joy to do this.</i>

515
00:35:49.414 --> 00:35:51.110
[DEVICE WHIRRING]

516
00:36:00.325 --> 00:36:02.089
<i>But it wasn't enough.</i>

517
00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:04.525
[ISABELLA GROANS
AND PIERO GASPS]

518
00:36:08.133 --> 00:36:12.127
<i>I told Piero to grind the flesh.
blood. and bone into the pigment.</i>

519
00:36:12.671 --> 00:36:15.835
<i>I had completely become
one with the painting...</i>

520
00:36:16.007 --> 00:36:18.476
<i>- and with Piero.</i>
- "And with Piero."

521
00:36:43.868 --> 00:36:48.329
She got to Father Delaney. She's around
here. We gotta get you out of here. Come on.

522
00:36:48.506 --> 00:36:51.203
[GRUNTING]

523
00:36:56.247 --> 00:36:58.443
[GRUNTING]

524
00:37:08.526 --> 00:37:09.960
[BOTH GRUNTING]

525
00:37:11.863 --> 00:37:17.393
The priest had to die. He made
it his business to forgive you pigs.

526
00:37:17.569 --> 00:37:21.233
Forgive you when what
you do is unforgivable.

527
00:37:21.406 --> 00:37:23.375
Sam. burn the journal.

528
00:37:41.860 --> 00:37:43.954
[GASPING]

529
00:37:46.564 --> 00:37:47.862
[WHIMPERING]

530
00:37:54.572 --> 00:37:58.134
Sister. Don't let them.
You are my friend.

531
00:38:00.378 --> 00:38:01.744
[SCREAMING]

532
00:38:13.658 --> 00:38:15.024
[CHUCKLES]

533
00:38:15.193 --> 00:38:17.685
You're... You're trucking.

534
00:38:19.030 --> 00:38:20.054
Is that her?

535
00:38:20.899 --> 00:38:23.869
Poetic justice. if you ask me.

536
00:38:24.035 --> 00:38:26.334
For hundreds of years.
those hags made me grovel.

537
00:38:26.504 --> 00:38:28.973
Every attempt to
please them. futile.

538
00:38:29.140 --> 00:38:33.601
High time someone
else ran in circles. eh?

539
00:38:34.879 --> 00:38:37.542
Nice touch. Something I
might have thought of myself.

540
00:38:38.149 --> 00:38:41.210
You see? We're
not so very different.

541
00:38:41.386 --> 00:38:44.083
What is it that you want?

542
00:38:44.255 --> 00:38:46.656
Ah. Well. Fergus.
since you asked...

543
00:38:46.825 --> 00:38:51.559
these friends of yours.
the Winchesters...

544
00:38:51.729 --> 00:38:54.255
I hear they are...
What do you call it?

545
00:38:54.432 --> 00:38:55.900
Men of Letters?

546
00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:57.734
Possibly.

547
00:38:57.902 --> 00:39:01.236
- I see. Well. about that...
- Listen. we've been through this.

548
00:39:01.406 --> 00:39:04.240
My relationship with the
Winchesters is my business.

549
00:39:04.409 --> 00:39:06.571
I'll handle them.
I'm not killing them.

550
00:39:07.912 --> 00:39:10.677
All right. dearie. Of course.

551
00:39:11.382 --> 00:39:13.874
Whatever you say.

552
00:39:29.434 --> 00:39:32.165
Who mixes their blood
and bones into paint?

553
00:39:32.937 --> 00:39:35.406
No woman's ever
done that for me.

554
00:39:35.874 --> 00:39:40.209
Is this you thanking me for not
doing what you told me to do?

555
00:39:40.378 --> 00:39:44.577
You know. if you'd have burned the journal.
we wouldn't know how to kill her. would we?

556
00:39:44.749 --> 00:39:48.186
Heh. Yeah. you're welcome.

557
00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:51.287
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

558
00:39:55.260 --> 00:39:56.785
You know...

559
00:39:57.495 --> 00:40:00.556
you were in that
confessional a long time.

560
00:40:06.337 --> 00:40:08.465
Look. man. I'm just saying...

561
00:40:08.907 --> 00:40:10.307
I'm your brother. Dean.

562
00:40:10.475 --> 00:40:13.274
If you ever need to talk
about anything with anybody...

563
00:40:13.444 --> 00:40:16.107
you got somebody
right here next to you.

564
00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:20.912
Okay.

565
00:40:22.287 --> 00:40:25.018
I heard what Sister Mathias
was saying about. you know...

566
00:40:26.424 --> 00:40:28.859
hiding pain by
taking on a mission...

567
00:40:29.027 --> 00:40:32.259
and I know that's what
you're doing. a little bit.

568
00:40:32.430 --> 00:40:37.130
And it's okay. I mean. it's fine.
I get it. I've done it before too.

569
00:40:38.803 --> 00:40:43.935
But I don't buy for one second
that the Mark is a terminal diagnosis.

570
00:40:44.642 --> 00:40:48.010
So don't go making
peace with that idea.

571
00:40:48.179 --> 00:40:52.310
There has to be a way. There
will be a way. and we will find it.

572
00:40:52.483 --> 00:40:54.281
That's what we do.

573
00:40:54.886 --> 00:40:56.252
So believe that.

574
00:40:58.156 --> 00:41:00.148
Okay. Sammy.

575
00:41:02.493 --> 00:41:04.121
You wanna...

576
00:41:04.996 --> 00:41:07.192
try that again like you mean it?

577
00:41:10.301 --> 00:41:11.963
Okay.

578
00:41:55.813 --> 00:41:57.805
[English - US -SDH]

578
00:41:58.305 --> 00:42:58.262
